1. Xinhuanet published an article introducing stablecoins. Issuers of stablecoins can include large e-commerce companies and licensed financial institutions;
2. Musk's old Instagram account is suspected to be auctioned, and fraudulent Meme coins may be launched;
3. Binance Alpha is in decline, and yesterday's trading volume of US$487 million has dropped 70% from the high point;
4. Web3 game company SpekterGames completed a US$5 million Pre-seed round of financing, led by a16zSpeedrun;
5. SharpLink Gaming purchased another 1,989 ETH through OTC, worth US$4.82 million;
6. Trump: If I had known that the US president was a "high-risk job", I might not have run for election;
7. NOYA.ai had a security vulnerability, and the official called for a suspension of use. The accident was caused by the behavior of internal developers;
8. BlackRock purchased US$1.15 billion worth of Bitcoin this week;
9. More than US$2.1 billion in crypto assets were stolen in the first half of 2025, 70% of which came from hacker groups related to North Korea.
